A football changing room is being kitted out to be used as a community centre.More than £30,000 is to be spent renovating part of the football facilities at Kirk Hallam’s Windsor Crescent park.A section of the changing room block next to the play area will become a space for the wider community to use.The funding for Erewash Borough Council to carry out the project follows calls from the Kirk Hallam Community Wellness Foundation for a new youth and community space in the area.
Councillor Josy Hare said: “With money being so tight for the council I pay tribute to our team for managing to find outside funding for this project.“It means that the residents of Kirk Hallam are getting a crucial new space for the community to make use of.”Richard Smith, senior grant manager at the FCC Communities Foundation, which is financing the scheme, said: “We’re delighted to be supporting the conversion – and pleased our funding will make such a difference to so many groups of people.“FCC Communities Foundation is looking forward to this project having a positive impact very soon.”Follow BBC Derby on Facebook, on X, or on Instagram. Send your story ideas to eastmidsnews@bbc.co.uk or via WhatsApp on 0808 100 2210.
